    That was my take.  The patch text actually claimed that the mysterious dual wield equation &quot;takes several factors into account&quot;, but says that pets summoned from the level 34 spell have a slight chance to DW, and ones from the 39 spell have a slight change not to.  Since the original two ranges of those spells overlapped at 30 (best pet for 34, next-to-worst for 39), I took the phrasing to mean that a level 30 pet can automatically DW without weapons, satisfying the claims of the patch text.  The only time you're _certain_ to get a pet higher than 30 is from a level 44 summons.  You're nearly certain with the level 39, plus or minus the other unspecified &quot;several factors&quot;.<br>
<br>
   Later, Absor claimed that Verant revised spells which could summon pets both above and below 36th level.  36 is a fairly magical point for NPCs, apparently, where among other things they get noticably increased regen.  Apparently they liked the power level of the 36+ pets, but not the 35- ones for that level of summons (44 for a mage), so they changed the spell to always summon at least a 36th pet.  Thus, level 44 summons should now always be well above the minimums needed to DW automatically.<br>
<br>
   You might still give your pets weapons as a means of buffing their stats at those levels, or you might give them a weapon with a proc.  But pets are supposed to DW without weapons after that point.  From level 24 summons until then, weapons will be needed to activate the DW ability, just as they have been since they almost fixed the DW bug.<br>
